  "monologue": "From a CBT perspective, a quick post-meal reflection reinforces cue detection and reduces decision fatigue after a meal, especially for someone who needs structure and is sensitive to evening triggers. By anchoring a tiny, measurable check (fullness rating and a single supportive factor), you build confidence and create a clear path to small, doable tweaks rather than all-or-nothing changes.",
  "utterance": "Tonight's fresh nudge: after finishing your one-plate meal, take 60 seconds to rate your fullness (0-10) and name one factor that helped you stay on track (e.g., slow eating, veggies on the plate, or the mindful pause). Then commit to one tiny tweak for tomorrowâ€”such as adding one more veggie at the next meal, or doing a 1-minute reset before considering seconds. This keeps the plate approach steady, honors your structure, and slowly nudges you toward your next milestone.",
  "endkey": false
}
